title: Urgent bid to stop work on Brisbane Olympic stadium rejected
description: The Brisbane Olympic stadium has survived the bid to halt it on cultural grounds.  Early works will continue at Victoria Park for a 63,000-seat stadium that will be the centrepiece of the Olympic Games in 2032.  Federal Environment Minister Murray Watt has the power to protect significant cultural heritage sites, but has rejected an urgent application to stop work.

title: 'The View' co-hosts have collective meltdown after Trump hilariously flips off heckler
description: ‘The View’ co-hosts have had yet another meltdown over US President Donald Trump’s hilarious response to a heckler.  During a Ford factory visit on Tuesday, a heckler called Trump a “paedophile protector” before the president mouthed “f*** you” and flipped him off.  The president’s actions were praised by his supporters on social media, with many finding Trump’s response hilarious.  Co-hosts on The View, however, didn’t find the funny side as Joy Behar and Sunny Hostin claimed Trump’s response was unpresidential.  “Trump flipped him the bird a couple of times and used the "F" word on him. That is not what I call presidential,” Behar said.  “In my lifetime, and that goes back to Jefferson, I have never heard a president use the ‘F’ word or flip the bird on an American citizen, a person, a person.”

title: Trump blasts ‘China-centric’ people who opened Supreme Court tariffs case
description: ​US President Donald Trump has criticised the Supreme Court’s dispute over the legality of his global tariff scheme.  “I can’t believe we even have a case. This was a case started by very China-centric people and also anti-American people,” Mr Trump said.  “Tariffs have helped us stop eight wars … above all else, they’ve given us tremendous national security.”

title: Trump slams lacklustre Greenland defence as Denmark fails to 'change' president's mind
description: US President Donald Trump has slammed Denmark's defensive capability as he doubles down on his bid to take control of Greenland.  "Greenland is very important for the national security, including of Denmark. And the problem is there's not a thing that Denmark can do about it if Russia or China wants to occupy Greenland. But there's everything we can do," Trump told reporters on Wednesday.  It comes as Denmark vowed on Wednesday to expand its military presence in Greenland.  “Now we are going to have a larger military footprint, and we are doing so because we believe it is the right thing to do," Danish Defence Minister Troels Lund Poulsen said.  "Also, in relation to the need to have a greater degree of presence together with other NATO allies.  "This is also something that we have discussed continuously in NATO over the past two years, where I myself have strongly argued that NATO needs to take a greater interest in security, to become a part of the NATO framework.”  The remarks came after high-stakes meetings between US, Danish, and Greenlandic officials.  Denmark’s Foreign Minister Lars Lokke Rasmussen said fundamental differences over Greenland remained.  “We didn't manage to change the American position," Rasmussen said.

title: ‘Doomsday glacier’: Underwater tsunamis in Antarctica causing havoc
description: Scientists in Antarctica are investigating underwater tsunamis triggered by the collapse of ice.  Experts are deploying submarine drones deep beneath the surface to analyse the waves’ effect on melting glaciers.  A team of scientists has landed on the “infamous” Thwaites Glacier, nicknamed the “Doomsday Glacier,” to conduct research.

title: Hilarious moment senator humiliates progressive doctor after asking ‘can men get pregnant’
description: There has been a war of words on Capitol Hill today after Senator Josh Hawley asked Dr Nisha Verma if men can get pregnant.

title: ‘Leave Iran urgently’: Tehran closes its airspace anticipating US attack
description: Sky News Asia correspondent Stas Butler breaks down the evidence the United States may launch an attack on Iran.  “The biggest evidence at the very least that there’s severe international concern about a potential attack is the closure by Iran of its airspace to most civilian traffic except that which has been authorised by Iran,” Mr Butler told Sky News Australia.  “Several western countries, including the US, UK, Italy, and Poland, among others, have asked their citizens to leave Iran urgently.  “The US has reportedly closed its embassy in Tehran.”

title: ‘It’s a new world’: Greenlanders feel ‘afraid’ and ‘worried’ over Trump’s takeover threat
description: Greenland University Head of Department Aviaq Fleischer has revealed how Greenlanders feel about US President Donald Trump’s repeated threat to acquire the Arctic territory.  “We have felt all the feelings here in Greenland. Some are afraid, some are worried, but myself, I refuse to let myself be affected by what Mr Trump is doing to our society,” she told Sky News Australia.  “We feel empowered.  “It’s a new world.”

title: Germany and Sweden send military personnel to Greenland amid Trump threat
description: Germany and Sweden have announced they will send military personnel to Greenland as US President Donald Trump continues his push for the Arctic territory to become part of America.  President Trump raised concerns about Russian and Chinese military goals for Greenland.  Meanwhile, the European Union’s President has come out in support of Greenland’s sovereignty, ensuring citizens can count on them.

title: Europe sends ‘more soldiers’ over to Greenland amid Trump’s takeover threat
description: Greenland University Head of Department Aviaq Fleischer has responded to US President Donald Trump’s claims that the Arctic territory’s defence is “dogsleds”.  “There is military here, and more soldiers are flying over from Europe,” she told Sky News Australia.  “But it’s usually a very peaceful land, and it’s a new world.”

title: ‘Abject failure of leadership’: Albanese ‘not leading’ Australia towards social cohesion
description: Shadow Energy and Emissions Reduction Minister Dan Tehan claims Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has shown an “abject failure of leadership” on social cohesion.  “What we are seeing is more and more division,” Mr Tehan told Sky News Australia.   “That is on the hands of the prime minister because he is failing to lead us through this crisis.”

title: ‘Agree to disagree on Greenland’: Trump admin officials and foreign ministers meet
description: A tense meeting between the US and the foreign ministers of Greenland and Denmark has ended in both sides agreeing to disagree.   America is still forging ahead with its intention to secure Greenland, believing the Arctic region is in danger from Russia and China.  Danish Foreign Minister Lars Lokke Rasmussen referred to the talks as frank but constructive.  Denmark has ramped up its military presence around Greenland as US President Trump ramps up his rhetoric around taking control of Greenland.  President Trump hasn’t ruled out military action to gain Greenland, though US Secretary of State Marco Rubio says the American leader wants to buy, not take over the country with force.

title: ‘Chip off the old block’: Albanese emulating Dan Andrews with political ‘games’
description: Shadow Energy and Emissions Reduction Minister Dan Tehan claims Anthony Albanese is playing “blatant politics” with Labor's new hate speech bill.  “Everyone has seen it for what it is, it's blatant politics,” Mr Tehan told Sky News Australia.   “It’s time the prime minister acted like a true leader during a national crisis, instead of these games.  “It’s the way Dan Andrews used to lead in Victoria, and it’s like he’s a chip off the old block.”

title: Trump reminds Iran he 'blew them up' in chilling reply to country's threat
description: US President Donald Trump has issued a chilling warning to Iran, reminding the regime he had previously “blown them up".  The remarks came as Tehran has threatened to strike American bases in neighbouring countries if Washington intervenes over its violent crackdown on anti-regime protesters, a senior Iranian official told Reuters.  Speaking to reporters at Joint Base Andrews in Maryland on Tuesday, Trump warned Iran to "behave" or face the consequences.  “Iran said that the last time I blew them up, with the nuclear capability, which they don't have any longer. So Iran said that the last time, they better behave," he said.

title: 'Coward' Hakeem Jeffries refuses to answer questions on calls to defund ICE
description: House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries has been heavily scrutinised online for refusing to answer questions about ICE.  Jeffries was pressed on the recent call by Democrats to abolish ICE, with the party proposing a new bill.  A journalist questioned Jeffries if he supported the bill to abolish ICE, to which he said he hadn’t “had a conversation” on the legislation.  Social media was quick to attack Jeffries, many labelling him a “coward” and “liar” for not standing with law enforcement.  “@RepJeffries is a coward who does not stand with law enforcement officers,” one user wrote.
